KATSINA – Bandits have killed chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Sabuwa Local Government Area of Katsina State, Alhaji Lawal Dako. According to Katsina Post, Dako was shot by bandits on November 8 but died on Friday, November 20 from injuries sustained as a result of the attack. He died at the Ahmadu Bello University Teaching Hospital. Katsina is one of the states with a high rate of insecurity in Nigeria. (Independent) A Nigerian soldier has died while he was trying to rescue a nursing mother from bandits in Katsina.   According to The PUNCH, the Operation Sahel Sanity troops based in Faskari Local Government Area, Katsina State, lost a soldier who tried to rescue the nursing mother during a gun duel… November 1, 2020 In "News" A Press Release which was signed by the Spokesman of the State Police Command, Superintendent Gambo Isa, and made available to newsmen, said the bandits in their numbers on motorcycles invaded the house of Alhaji Tasiu Wali in Jibia town He said ‘’ his wife Hajiya Asmau Tasiu was abducted… December 30, 2019 In "News" By Abdullahi Shugaba Katsina - The Emir of Kano, Alhaji Aminu Bayero has commiserated with the people and Government of Katsina state over the passing of Malam Wada Maida, former Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). Maida, a serving Chairman of the NAN Board of Directors, died… August 19, 2020 In "News"